The '''SR Class LN''' or '''''' is a class of   designed for the  by .  Intended for express passenger work to the South-West of .  Sixteen of this type were constructed at Southern's  between 1926 and 1929; they represented the ultimate in Southern 4-6-0 design.  They followed Southern Railway practice of naming their express passenger types, in this case after famous admirals.  The class continued to operate with  until 1961, after modifications were made to the blastpipe by .  The class was withdrawn in 1961, and only one example of the class has been preserved.  ''Lord Nelson'' can be seen running on mainline tours throughout Britain.